    {
      "id": "1245155652649881641",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-05-29T08:24:01.465+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "The fact that it has quite impressive strength scaling helps it a lot to fit it into different types of decks. It's good in a Dead on deck because that deck type usually lacks multihit attacks for big strength payout. It's good in a curse decks because you're usually able to survive long enough to scale it up in damage and get some strength from determination. It's obviously great with any source of cost manipulation, especially <Gambit> witch lets you both scale it's damage and frontload it with potentially getting to play desperado twice on the same turn",
      "author": {
